// The search works through these main components:

1. State Management:
- searchTerm state to track user input
- filteredSkills state to store filtered results

2. Search Logic:
The filtering happens through useEffect that watches for searchTerm changes:
- Matches both title and description
- Case-insensitive search
- Combined with other filters (category, level, etc.)

Here's the key search implementation from SearchPage.tsx:

const filtered = ALL_SKILLS_DATA.filter((skill) => {
  // Search matches title or description
  const matchesSearch = skill.title.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm.toLowerCase()) ||
    skill.description.toLowerCase().includes(searchTerm.toLowerCase());

  // Additional filter conditions
  const matchesCategory = filters.category === 'All Categories' ||
    skill.category.toLowerCase() === filters.category.toLowerCase();
  
  const matchesLevel = filters.level === 'All Levels' ||
    skill.level.toLowerCase() === filters.level.toLowerCase();

  // Combined conditions
  return matchesSearch && matchesCategory && matchesLevel;
});